{
  "text": "Source: [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] also demonstrate in this figure that real practice might not be neat as this spiral containing planning, acting, observing, and reflecting suggests. These stages will overlap, and initial plans will become obsolete in the light of learning from experience. In fact, the process is likely to be more fluid, open, and responsive. Furthermore, the success of this action plan does not depend on the faithfully following these steps, but is achievable through a strong sense of evolution and development in the researcher's practices and understandings.",
